---
import PageShell from '../../../../components/PageShell.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'overview', text: 'Overview', level: 2 },
  { id: 'healthcare-system', text: 'Healthcare System', level: 2 },
  { id: 'visa-requirements', text: 'Visa Options', level: 2 },
  { id: 'insurance-requirements', text: 'Insurance Requirements', level: 2 },
  { id: 'recommended-providers', text: 'Recommended Providers', level: 2 },
  { id: 'costs', text: 'Expected Costs', level: 2 },
  { id: 'scenarios', text: 'Real-World Scenarios', level: 2 },
  { id: 'faqs', text: 'Common Questions', level: 2 },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { title: 'Panama Insurance Guide', href: '/countries/panama/insurance' },
  { title: 'Insurance for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors' },
  { title: 'Costa Rica for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/costa-rica' },
  { title: 'Ecuador for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/ecuador' },
  { title: 'Colombia for Seniors', href: '/insurance-for/seniors/in/colombia' },
];

const providerColumns = [
  { key: 'provider', header: 'Provider' },
  { key: 'entryAge', header: 'Max Entry Age' },
  { key: 'renewal', header: 'Renewal' },
  { key: 'monthlyFrom', header: 'From (65-69)' },
  { key: 'panamaFit', header: 'Panama Fit' },
];

const providerRows = [
  { provider: 'Cigna Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$370-530/mo', panamaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'BUPA Global', entryAge: '79', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$435-620/mo', panamaFit: 'Excellent' },
  { provider: 'GeoBlue', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'Lifetime', monthlyFrom: '$340-490/mo', panamaFit: 'Very Good' },
  { provider: 'IMG Global', entryAge: '74', renewal: 'To 80', monthlyFrom: '$310-450/mo', panamaFit: 'Good' },
  { provider: 'Panamanian Local', entryAge: '65', renewal: 'Annual', monthlyFrom: '$150-400/mo', panamaFit: 'Limited' },
];

const costColumns = [
  { key: 'category', header: 'Expense' },
  { key: 'monthly', header: 'Monthly' },
  { key: 'annual', header: 'Annual' },
];

const costRows = [
  { category: 'International Insurance (65-69)', monthly: '$340-530', annual: '$4,080-6,360' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (70-74)', monthly: '$470-700', annual: '$5,640-8,400' },
  { category: 'International Insurance (75-79)', monthly: '$640-950', annual: '$7,680-11,400' },
  { category: 'Panama Private Hospital', monthly: 'Pay per visit', annual: '$50-120/visit' },
  { category: 'Panama CSS (public)', monthly: 'Limited access', annual: 'For contributors' },
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Health Insurance for Seniors in Panama 2026 | Retirement Guide"
  description="Guide to health insurance for seniors retiring in Panama. Famous Pensionado visa, USD currency, excellent healthcare, and coverage for expats 65+."
  headline="Health Insurance for Seniors in Panama"
  subheadline="Panama offers world-famous Pensionado visa, USD currency, excellent JCI-accredited hospitals, and legendary senior discounts—a top retirement destination for Americans."
  heroImage="/images/countries/panama-hero-bg.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
  ctaButtonText="Compare Senior Plans →"
  ctaButtonHref="/go/cigna-global"
>
  <h2 id="overview">Why Seniors Choose Panama</h2>
  <p>
    Panama invented the pensionado visa—the world first retirement visa program. USD currency, excellent healthcare (JCI-accredited hospitals), generous senior discounts, and strategic Americas location make it a perennial top retirement destination.
  </p>

  <p>
    Panama City offers modern living with excellent hospitals. Boquete in the highlands provides spring-like climate and established expat community. Coronado and Pacific beaches offer coastal retirement. Bocas del Toro attracts adventurous types with Caribbean vibe.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-primary-900 mb-3">Key Facts for Seniors</h3>
    <ul class="text-primary-800 space-y-2">
      <li><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Excellent; JCI-accredited hospitals in Panama City</li>
      <li><strong>Language:</strong> Spanish; English common in expat areas</li>
      <li><strong>Cost of Living:</strong> $1,500-3,500/month; moderate-high for region</li>
      <li><strong>Currency:</strong> USD (no exchange risk for Americans)</li>
      <li><strong>Senior Discounts:</strong> 25% off flights, restaurants, entertainment, more</li>
      <li><strong>Character:</strong> Modern; cosmopolitan; Americas hub</li>
    </ul>
  </div>

  <h2 id="healthcare-system">Panama Healthcare System</h2>
  <p>
    Panama has excellent healthcare—JCI-accredited hospitals like Hospital Punta Pacifica (affiliated with Johns Hopkins), Hospital Nacional, and Clinica Hospital San Fernando provide world-class care. Many doctors US-trained. Medical tourism is growing.
  </p>

  <p>
    Outside Panama City, quality drops. Boquete has limited facilities; serious cases require Panama City. Public healthcare (CSS) exists but is overcrowded—not recommended for expats.
  </p>

  <div class="bg-amber-50 border border-amber-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-amber-900 mb-2">Johns Hopkins Affiliation</h3>
    <p class="text-amber-800 mb-0">
      Hospital Punta Pacifica is affiliated with Johns Hopkins International—bringing US healthcare protocols to Panama. Costs are 40-60% below US.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="visa-requirements">Visa Options for Seniors</h2>
  <p>
    Panama offers the world most famous retirement visa:
  </p>

  <h3>Pensionado Visa (Jubilado/Pensionado)</h3>
  <p>
    The original retirement visa—requires $1,000+/month guaranteed pension income (Social Security qualifies). Permanent residence. Famous senior discounts (25% off flights, restaurants, entertainment, utilities, more).
  </p>

  <h3>Friendly Nations Visa</h3>
  <p>
    For citizens of 50+ friendly nations—easier pathway requiring economic ties (employment, business, or $5,000 bank deposit).
  </p>

  <h3>Investment Visa</h3>
  <p>
    Property investment of $300,000+ or business investment qualifies for residence.
  </p>

  <h2 id="insurance-requirements">Insurance Requirements</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance requirements for Panama:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pensionado visa:</strong> Health insurance not technically required but strongly recommended</li>
    <li><strong>Practical need:</strong> Private coverage essential for quality care</li>
    <li><strong>US evacuation:</strong> Miami is 2.5 hours away; include US coverage</li>
    <li><strong>JCI hospitals:</strong> Ensure coverage at Panama City top facilities</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200 rounded-lg p-4 my-6">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-blue-900 mb-2">Insurance Strategy for Panama</h3>
    <p class="text-blue-800 mb-0">
      International insurance is recommended for Panama seniors—local insurers have age limits. Panama City healthcare is excellent but insurance ensures access to JCI hospitals and US evacuation if needed.
    </p>
  </div>

  <h2 id="recommended-providers">Recommended Insurance Providers</h2>
  <p>
    For seniors in Panama, international coverage with US access works well:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={providerColumns} rows={providerRows} />

  <h3>Why These Providers Work for Panama</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Cigna Global:</strong> Good Americas network, US evacuation included</li>
    <li><strong>BUPA Global:</strong> Highest entry age (79), comprehensive coverage</li>
    <li><strong>GeoBlue:</strong> Blue Cross network for US visits (Miami access)</li>
    <li><strong>IMG Global:</strong> Budget-friendly with decent coverage</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Get Personalized Senior Quotes</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Compare coverage from providers popular with Panama expats.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="costs">Expected Insurance Costs</h2>
  <p>
    Insurance costs for Panama are moderate given excellent healthcare quality:
  </p>

  <ComparisonTable columns={costColumns} rows={costRows} />

  <h3>Cost-Saving Strategies</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Higher deductibles:</strong> Panama private care is affordable</li>
    <li><strong>Pay cash routine:</strong> Private consultations $50-80</li>
    <li><strong>Americas-only:</strong> Skip worldwide coverage if not traveling globally</li>
    <li><strong>Miami option:</strong> Include US for complex care evacuation</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 id="scenarios">Real-World Scenarios</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 1: American Social Security Retiree, 68</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> $1,500/month Social Security. Seeking USD country with good healthcare.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pensionado visa. Cigna Global with US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> Cigna ~$420/month. JCI-accredited care; senior discounts; Miami 2.5 hours away.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 2: Canadian Highland Couple, Both 72</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> Combined pension CAD 3,800/month. Retiring to Boquete.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pensionado visas. BUPA Global for both.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> BUPA ~$1,100/month combined. Spring-like climate; good healthcare access.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-3">Scenario 3: British Beach Retiree, 66</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Situation:</strong> £2,000/month pension. Retiring to Coronado beach.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-2"><strong>Solution:</strong> Pensionado via UK pension. GeoBlue with UK + US coverage.</p>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0"><strong>Cost:</strong> GeoBlue ~$400/month (~£320). Pacific beach; senior discounts.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2 id="faqs">Common Questions</h2>

  <div class="space-y-6 my-8">
    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">What are Panama famous senior discounts?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Excellent: 25% off flights, 25% off restaurants (Mon-Thu), 15-25% off hotels, 25% off electricity, 50% off entertainment, 20% off medical consultations, 15% off hospital services. Discounts for women 55+ and men 60+.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">How does Panama healthcare compare to US?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        JCI-accredited Panama City hospitals rival US quality. Hospital Punta Pacifica (Johns Hopkins affiliate) offers US-standard care at 40-60% cost. Miami is 2.5 hours away for complex cases.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Boquete a good retirement choice?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Popular—spring-like climate (15-25C year-round), established expat community, beautiful mountains. Downsides: limited healthcare (serious cases need Panama City 6+ hours).
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="border-b border-neutral-200 pb-4">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Is Panama City expensive?</h3>
      <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-0">
        Moderate—more expensive than Ecuador but less than US. Good apartment $1,200-2,500/month. Overall $2,000-3,500/month for comfortable lifestyle.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-primary-50 border border-primary-200 rounded-lg p-6 my-8">
    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-neutral-900 mb-2">Ready to Compare Options?</h3>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-4">Get quotes from providers with Americas coverage for Panama retirement.</p>
    <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
      <a href="/go/cigna-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-primary-600 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-primary-700 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get Cigna Quote</a>
      <a href="/go/bupa-global" class="inline-block px-5 py-2.5 bg-neutral-700 text-white rounded-lg hover:bg-neutral-800 transition-colors font-medium" style="color: white !important;">Get BUPA Quote</a>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-neutral-50 border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6 mt-8">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 mb-0">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for informational purposes only. Insurance requirements, visa regulations, and healthcare access rules change regularly. Always verify current requirements with Panamanian authorities and consult with a licensed insurance professional.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
